sql:
SELECT SUM(fully_vaccinated) AS total_fully_vaccinated
FROM vaccination_stats
WHERE age_group_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Vaccination coverage refers to the percentage of the population that has received the required doses of a vaccine to be considered fully vaccinated; 
- In this context, age groups are categorized based on age ranges, and regions are geographical areas; 
- Fully vaccinated individuals are those who have received all recommended doses of a vaccine.
